reviews.text: This restaurant has been a treat. The food was delicious! As someone who doesn‚Äôt have a big appetite, the grilled sea bass was a perfect small portion and cooked to perfection. Make sure you leave room for dessert and order the blueberry pie bar‚Äî I have never had such a delicious dessert! We ate it so quickly we didn‚Äôt get a picture. Ask for Kanon to serve you‚Äî he is an excellent waiter, and he‚Äôs easy on the eyes!

We visited a couple of weeks ago to celebrate a friend‚Äôs birthday and had a truly wonderful experience. The service was exceptional‚Äîour server was incredibly sweet, attentive, and welcoming. She was expecting at the time, and still made sure everything ran smoothly.

The ambiance was elegant and relaxing, with tasteful d√©cor that set a pleasant tone for the evening.

We sampled a variety of martinis; the espresso martini and lemon drop martini stood out as our favorites‚Äîboth were well-balanced and expertly crafted.

For appetizers, we ordered a cheese board and crispy cauliflower. The cheese board offered a delightful combination of sweet and savory flavors, while the cauliflower was perfectly crispy and paired beautifully with a sweet citrus chili sauce.

For my entr√©e, I had the salmon, which was cooked to perfection. My friends enjoyed their dishes as well, including burgers and another entr√©e that were both flavorful and satisfying.

To finish the evening, we shared the cheesecake and mixed berry cobbler. Both desserts were excellent, but the cheesecake was especially memorable.

Overall, this was an outstanding dining experience. We‚Äôre already looking forward to our next visit.

Best place for a girls night out OR date night!
Delicious appetizers, especially the fried cauliflower!
Delicious salads, especially the charcuterie salad AND southwest salad! Mmm!
And the tomato basil soup was heavenly!
Prices are high, but it's totally worth it.
